<p>
<font size = +1>PART FOUR: ASK MR SMARTYPANTS</font><br>
<p>
Out of the few emails I got since my first post, this one was the funniest.<br>
<p>
Mr Smartypants,<br>
<p>
Who are the people in EQ that influenced you the most?<br>
<p>
Anonymous<br>
<p>
Well, Anonymous, the first thing I can tell you is that if you send an anonymous email, don't use an email address with what is obviously your EQ character's name.  
It kinda makes the whole "anonymous" thing not quite as effective.  <br>
<p>
Regardless, I will answer your question.  I don't think anyone really INFLUENCED me at all in EQ.  I mean, I have some people who made EQ fun, but I honestly cannot say 
anyone influenced me.  Although, there are a few people that really kept my energy high, and a few people I would thank along the way for giving me some good insights 
and laughs.  <br>
<p>
For example, thanks to LARINY for letting me use your password so we could look at the Nightbane boards.  Got some really good stuff from there, and I appreciate it.  
It's a shame they booted you from Night Eternal, though.<br>
<p>
Another person I would thank would be ZFALCON.  Every time I needed someone to be my bitch, there you were.  Thanks.  Probably one of the funniest egomaniacal liars of 
all time.  Don't get me wrong, I don't miss you one bit.  I just enjoyed watching your foot as you tried to talk around it.<br>
<p>
And hmmm who else?  In GH, I would have to thank HOOLOOVU.  A strange person, but fun as hell to torture people with.  If you ever want to hear a creative use of the 
English language, talk to Hoo.<br>
<p>
Oh and I can't forget STORMBEARD.  In some ways it's too bad that we never really got into a heated argument.  At least he would have given me a run for my money.  
I'm betting his posts made me laugh more than mine did for him. <br>
<p>
Finally, I would have to thank the awesome people who would send me all the inside dirt on your guilds.  It really made some of my more memorable posts just amazingly 
easy.  I always enjoyed watching some of the ego filled shitheads spluttering and fuming when you helped me spill all the good juicy bits of their idiocy to the rest 
of the world.  Remember kids, people LOVE to see others fail.  It makes for great drama.  When you treat others like shit, don't be too shocked when those same people 
will ram that plug up your ass at the first available opportunity.<br>
<p>
Until next time!<br>
<p>
Mr. Smartypants<br>
